  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would like to add, for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the period of time that we live in right now, specifically viewing the situation in Israel, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that the world, the non-Jewish world, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] has very quickly forgotten. 50 years is quick.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To me, it is.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, it's flown by like nothing as what the world once did to annihilate 6 million Jewish people with women, men, and children.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They have a Holocaust center in Israel, just for a million and a half little babies that were killed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we're now on the verge of watching how this same UN, who jumped at that time, with Russia's first vote to declare Israel as a country are already now to give everything up and to-- instead of rebuild, to destroy everything that was so hardly-- hardly-- I mean, with hard efforts-- earned.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it looks to me, with my eyes at the world, that the world forgets too quick.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If you watch today Zaire, Yugoslavia, whatever-- these third-world countries-- people are starving to death.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People-- and people in the world, even though America I think is the most charitable country in the world.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But when you don't see it-- and some of them, even, we see it on television-- people just don't give a hoot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They keep on living.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it sounds to me-- to me, it sounds that the world-- the non-Jewish world-- I have to say there are always exceptions to the rule.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I don't like to put the whole world in one bundle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But for the purpose that I'm speaking now, I am saying that the non-Jewish world is more readily to feel bad for a killed Jew than for a live Jew.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, that's my personal opinion.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
